rComments: Lecture is ok, but he's a tough grader.

O' Brien is a pretty chill guy. He is a nice teacher and gives students no reason to dislike him. His class is easy too, just make sure not to skip the poem readings. Grade is based on attendance, so don't miss lecture.

O' Brien is a solid teacher. He's friendly, and he knows his stuff regarding Intro to Poetry. Sometimes a mumbler, its not really an issue because almost all of the class consists of analysis, so missing details doesn't hurt one at all.

He's so helpful and really knows how to teach. We discussed everything we had to read for homework & in class. O'Brien lets you voice your opinions and responds to you as an adult university student, which is refreshing. We read so many different interesting texts, this class was so enjoyable I'm going to miss it and O'Brien.
